GAME DESIGN — LAYER 3 COMPLETE
Wings Global Trade · Product Page · GAMIFY mode

================================================================
CORE LOOP — The Import Journey as Progression Arc
================================================================
Buyer fantasy: "I am a serious procurement professional who knows
exactly what I need." Every mechanic reinforces that fantasy. No
gamification theater. Mechanics serve buyer value, never platform
metrics.

MICRO (seconds):   Read spec → hover a value → learn WHY it matters
                   → feel more informed → dig deeper.
                   Drivers: ProductSpecTable hover reward + the
                   Spec Deep Dive reveal. The reward is knowledge,
                   not points.

MACRO (minutes):   Self-identify via ReasonChips ("Para carga
                   pesada" = recognition, not a feature badge) →
                   explore variants → ImportReadinessMeter advances
                   silently as the buyer moves toward submission →
                   open and submit the inquiry. The meter reads as
                   momentum toward a decision, not a form to fill.

META (days):       SavedInquiryBanner frames elapsed time as
                   service ("Guardamos tu selección hace N días") —
                   the platform held the buyer's work FOR them.
                   CatalogProgress frames the visit as the buyer's
                   own methodical evaluation, not as tracking.
                   The buyer returns because the experience felt
                   like expertise, not a catalog browse.

================================================================
AUDIT — What was enhanced and why
================================================================
- ImportReadinessMeter: was a pulsing loading-bar (anxiety: "is it
  loading?"). Rebuilt as MOMENTUM — only the leading edge animates,
  settled segments sit quiet, segments fill with a staggered
  cascade, and segment 5 (the submission/decision moment) carries
  extra visual weight via a subtle gold halo. The buyer is
  advancing toward a decision, not completing a progress bar.

- ReasonChips: were feature-badges (decorative ◆▲⊞ icons,
  ALL-CAPS, full gold border) reading as spec restatements.
  Stripped to SELF-IDENTIFICATION — every label now opens with
  "Para…" so the buyer reads it and recognizes their own
  operation ("that's me"), normal-case, quiet left-rule accent.
  Recognition over feature-listing.

- SavedInquiryBanner: 40ms animation (effectively invisible) and
  an underlined link + faded × that read like an ad to escape.
  Reframed as SERVICE — perceptible 320ms slide, elapsed-time
  framing ("Guardamos tu selección…"), "Retomar" as a soft filled
  action, dismiss relabeled "Empezar de nuevo" (a choice, not a
  trap). The platform works for the buyer, not to retain them.

- CatalogProgress: "Has explorado 3 de 5" read as surveillance.
  Reframed as the buyer's own EVALUATION — "Estás evaluando esta
  categoría", "Llevas N de M modelos revisados", "Has revisado
  toda la gama". Expertise, not a tracked counter.

================================================================
ProductSpecTable mechanics — COMPLETE:
  1. Spec Deep Dive Unlock: collapsed view shows only the 4
     priority specs (HP, payload, GVW, transmission, label-agnostic
     matching for snake_case + Spanish labels). "Ver
     especificaciones completas" toggle (DM Mono 10px gold, rotating
     chevron) reveals the rest. Revelation = micro-reward.
  2. Attention Reward on Hover: 1500ms dwell on a spec value with
     operational context (SPEC_CONTEXT) surfaces a DM Mono tooltip,
     gold left-rule, warm-white bg. Rewards the curious buyer with
     WHY the number matters. Timer cleared on leave + unmount.

  NOTE: This file was edited concurrently by the UX agent, who added
  a complementary click-to-inspect "Inspection Mode" (deep depth).
  Rather than clobber their work, both mechanics were reconciled into
  one coherent file: hover (quick knowledge reward) + click (deep
  investigation) + reveal (progressive disclosure). Full project
  typecheck passes clean (npx tsc --noEmit, 0 errors).
================================================================
